# .gitignore
# Vorathex — repo-level ignore rules.
#
# Rule of thumb: ignore anything a machine can regenerate, anything that is
# machine-local, and anything secret. Track everything that defines the build.
#
# Deliberately NOT ignored (do not "helpfully" add these later):
#   package-lock.json  — the reproducible-install contract. Committing it is the point.
#   .env.example       — documented, secret-free env template (Day 7).
#   .gitkeep           — the only thing keeping empty dirs in the tree.

# ── Dependencies ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
node_modules/
.npm/
.pnpm-store/

# ── Build output ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Anchored to the repo root: only /dist, never a src/**/dist we might mean to keep.
/dist/
*.tsbuildinfo

# ── Test output ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
/coverage/
.vitest-reports/
.vite/

# ── Secrets and local environment ───────────────────────────────────────────
# Broad ignore, then one surgical exception. Order matters: the negation must
# come after the pattern it overrides, or git never sees it.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# ── Logs ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*
logs/

# ── OS cruft ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# ── Editors / IDEs ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Note the trailing /* on .vscode — NOT .vscode/. A directory-level ignore cannot
# be un-ignored file-by-file, so this form is what makes the negations below work.
.vscode/*
!.vscode/settings.json
!.vscode/extensions.json
!.vscode/launch.json
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo

# ── Local scratch ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Anything you want to keep out of history without editing this file.
/tmp/
/scratch/
*.local
